{% set basicUsageCode %}<search-wc>
  <button data-trigger>
    <icon-wc name="search"></icon-wc>
    Search
  </button>
</search-wc>{% endset %}

{% set textTriggerCode %}<search-wc>
  <button data-trigger>Search</button>
</search-wc>{% endset %}

{% set iconOnlyTriggerCode %}<search-wc>
  <button data-trigger aria-label="Search">
    <icon-wc name="search"></icon-wc>
  </button>
</search-wc>{% endset %}

{% set keyboardHintTriggerCode %}<search-wc>
  <button data-trigger class="ghost">
    <icon-wc name="search" size="sm"></icon-wc>
    Search
    <kbd>Cmd+K</kbd>
  </button>
</search-wc>{% endset %}

{% set installPagefindCode %}npm install --save-dev pagefind{% endset %}

{% set buildScriptCode %}{
  "scripts": {
    "build": "vite build && npm run search:index",
    "search:index": "pagefind --site dist"
  }
}{% endset %}

{% set contentMarkingCode %}<main data-pagefind-body>
  <!-- Your content here -->
</main>{% endset %}

{% set excludeElementsCode %}<aside data-pagefind-ignore>
  <!-- This won't be indexed -->
</aside>{% endset %}

{% set pagefindConfigCode %}site: dist
output_subdir: pagefind

exclude_selectors:
  - "header"
  - "footer"
  - "nav"{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;search-wc&gt;</code> component provides a modal search interface with keyboard shortcuts, result highlighting, and keyboard navigation. It uses <a href="https://pagefind.app">Pagefind</a> for indexing and searching your static site content.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/search-wc-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/search"
      title="Search Component"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic search trigger">{{ basicUsageCode | safe }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Keyboard Shortcuts</h2>
    <p>The search component supports the following keyboard shortcuts:</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Shortcut</th>
          <th>Action</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Cmd</kbd> + <kbd>K</kbd> / <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>K</kbd></td>
          <td>Open/close search</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Escape</kbd></td>
          <td>Close search</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Arrow Up</kbd> / <kbd>Arrow Down</kbd></td>
          <td>Navigate results</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Enter</kbd></td>
          <td>Go to selected result</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Trigger Variants</h2>

    <h3>Text Button</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Text trigger">{{ textTriggerCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>Icon-Only Button</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Icon-only trigger">{{ iconOnlyTriggerCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>With Keyboard Hint</h3>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Trigger with keyboard hint">{{ keyboardHintTriggerCode | safe }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Default</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-open</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Reflected attribute indicating open state</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Events</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Event</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>search-wc-open</code></td>
          <td>Fired when search dialog opens</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>search-wc-close</code></td>
          <td>Fired when search dialog closes</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Pagefind Setup</h2>
    <p>The search component requires Pagefind to index your site content. Follow these steps to set up Pagefind:</p>

    <h3>1. Install Pagefind</h3>
    <code-block language="bash" show-lines label="Install as dev dependency">{{ installPagefindCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>2. Add Build Script</h3>
    <p>Add a script to run Pagefind after your site builds:</p>
    <code-block language="json" show-lines label="package.json scripts">{{ buildScriptCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>3. Mark Content Areas</h3>
    <p>Add <code>data-pagefind-body</code> to your main content areas to index them:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Content marking">{{ contentMarkingCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>4. Exclude Navigation</h3>
    <p>Navigation and chrome are automatically excluded. You can also explicitly exclude elements:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Excluding elements">{{ excludeElementsCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>5. Configuration (Optional)</h3>
    <p>Create a <code>pagefind.yml</code> for advanced configuration:</p>
    <code-block language="yaml" show-lines label="pagefind.yml">{{ pagefindConfigCode | safe }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Uses <code>role="dialog"</code> for the search modal</li>
      <li>Focus is trapped within the dialog when open</li>
      <li>Escape key closes the dialog and returns focus to trigger</li>
      <li>Results use <code>role="listbox"</code> and <code>role="option"</code></li>
      <li>Keyboard navigation through results with arrow keys</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
